{"sha": "3f0462acbbabc7703dffdd2771d6cca56eb5545b", "node_id": "MDY6Q29tbWl0NzI0NzEyOjNmMDQ2MmFjYmJhYmM3NzAzZGZmZGQyNzcxZDZjY2E1NmViNTU0NWI=", "commit": {"author": {"name": "Ulrich Weigand", "email": "ulrich.weigand@de.ibm.com", "date": "2016-09-07T15:21:10Z"}, "committer": {"name": "Ulrich Weigand", "email": "ulrich.weigand@de.ibm.com", "date": "2016-09-07T15:21:10Z"}, "message": "Fix argument to FIONBIO ioctl\n\nThe FIONBIO ioctl takes as argument a pointer to an integer, which\nshould be either 0 or 1 to indicate whether nonblocking mode is to\nbe switched off or on.  The type of the pointed-to variable is \"int\".\n\nHowever, the set_nonblocking routine in libstd/sys/unix/net.rs passes\na pointer to a libc::c_ulong variable.  This doesn't matter on all\n32-bit platforms and on all litte-endian platforms, but it will\nbreak on big-endian 64-bit platforms.\n\nFound while porting Rust to s390x (a big-endian 64-bit platform).\n\nSigned-off-by: Ulrich Weigand <ulrich.weigand@de.ibm.com>", "tree": {"sha": "6a57107cdb69e68da9f949e40de8cd64203dfb71", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/trees/6a57107cdb69e68da9f949e40de8cd64203dfb71"}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/commits/3f0462acbbabc7703dffdd2771d6cca56eb5545b", "comment_count": 0, "verification": {"verified": false, "reason": "unsigned", "signature": null, "payload": null}}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/3f0462acbbabc7703dffdd2771d6cca56eb5545b", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/commit/3f0462acbbabc7703dffdd2771d6cca56eb5545b", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/3f0462acbbabc7703dffdd2771d6cca56eb5545b/comments", "author": {"login": "uweigand", "id": 4154057, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjQxNTQwNTc=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/4154057?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/uweigand", "html_url": "https://github.com/uweigand", "followers_url": "https://